<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Grimshaw" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[238,565,901,927]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidicornis">
<emphasis box="[238,565,901,927]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Amblypsilopus pallidicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group has a broad range throughout the Oriental andAustralasian regions. The following Madagascan species belong to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Grimshaw" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[786,971,936,963]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidicornis">
<emphasis box="[786,971,936,963]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">A. pallidicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
